<figureCitation box="[352,429,1256,1278]" captionStart="Figs 75-85" captionStartId="24.[178,218,1502,1524]" captionTargetBox="[178,1076,212,1488]" captionTargetId="figure-1@24.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs 75-85: Nepalota mocytoides nov.sp.: (75) forebody; (76) antenna; (77) male tergite VIII; (78) male sternite VIII; (79-80) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (81) paramere; (82) female tergite VIII; (83) female sternite VIII; (84-85) spermatheca. Scale bars: 75: 0.5 mm; 76-85: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414202" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414202/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="230">Fig. 82</figureCitation>
