<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="232" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="25.[178,1085,219,329]" pageId="25" pageNumber="232">
Distribution and natural history: The type specimens were collected in two adjacent localities to the south of Jianshui, southern 
<collectingRegion box="[878,958,248,269]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="25" pageNumber="232">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[971,1040,248,270]" captionStart="Map 3" captionStartId="7.[178,223,811,832]" captionTargetBox="[178,1082,212,801]" captionTargetId="figure-1@7.[178,1082,212,801]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Map 3: Distributions of Nepalota franzi PACE (filled circles), N. mocytoides nov.sp. (open circle), and N. fellowesi PACE (filled triangles), based on examined and reliable literature records." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414163/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="232">Map 3</figureCitation>
), by sifting leaf litter in a subtropical broad-leaved forest and in a secondary forest margin at altitudes of 1890 and 
<quantity box="[397,476,307,328]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.81" pageId="25" pageNumber="232" unit="m" value="1810.0">1810 m</quantity>
, respectively. One of the 
<typeStatus box="[735,832,307,328]" pageId="25" pageNumber="232">paratypes</typeStatus>
is teneral.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
